<br>
Not everyone reads this board.  If you attempt to &quot;schedule&quot; a raid for Vox 48 hours after her spawn time, there is a pretty good chance some guild will notice she's up and jump in and killed her.<br>
<br>
There are plenty of people of the appropriate levels to take down both Vox and Naggy at the same time on the server, however, just like my first point, not everyone reads this board.  So I agree that there doesn't always seem to be enough people aware of the raids to deal with both of them.<br>
<br>
I think this is the problem that needs addressing, not the scheduling.  One way, is to limit the number of signups for each raid to a resonable number.  It doesn't really take 50 people to kill either dragon.  30 - 36 people is a reasonable number with a very high likelyhood of success.  I understand that not everyone who signs up, shows up.  But we could start referring signups to the other raid once more than 40 people have signed on.<br>
<br>
Co-operation is definately needed between both raids, and maybe your suggestion is the best way to handle it, but I believe that the longer you leave the spawn open, the higher the chances someone else will take it.<br>
<br>
